  "text": "Cardiorespiratory fitness. The Progressive Aerobic Cardiovascular Endurance Run (PACER) is a valid and reliable method for all ages and measured an individual's aerobic capacity [CITATION_1] .This test was administered according to the instructions outlined on the FITNESSGRAM CD (Cooper Institute for Aerobic Research, 2000) . The PACER test was a multistage fitness test set to music, with each stage getting progressively faster. Participants were instructed to run across the gym before the beep sounded on the audio CD. The test was terminated either due to exhaustion or because the participant was unable to reach the distance before the beep for two laps. The number of laps completed by each participant was recorded by staff for data analysis.",
